Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @Puff Pastry Sheet{1%pack} from your fridge and allow to come up to room temperature.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @Lamb Mince{200%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Stir in the garlic and @Korma Curry Paste{50%g} and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir through the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}. Simmer the sauce, until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from the heat, then stir through the @Peas{120%g} and @Honey{1%tbsp}. Set aside for later.

Meanwhile, halve the @Salad Potatoes{350%g} lengthways.

Pop the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle over the @White Cumin Seeds{1%sachet}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer, cut-side down.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, unroll the pastry, keeping it on its #baking paper{}, and lay it onto a baking tray. Cut it into equal squares (2 per person), trimming off any excess pastry to make them even.

Spoon your lamb mixture into the centre of each square. Fold the pastry over to create a triangle shape. Press in a #fork{} along the edges to seal the pastry closed - be careful not to overfill them!

> Brush the pastry with a little milk if you have some.

Make a small hole in the middle to allow steam to escape.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pickled Onion Salad ==

While everything cooks, halve, peel, and thinly slice the @Red Onion{½%unit}. Roughly chop the @Coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml} and @Sugar{1%tsp}. Add the sliced onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside to pickle.

In a small bowl, combine the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%g} and half the coriander. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix well.

== To Serve ==

Just before you're ready to serve, stir the olive oil through the pickled onion. Add @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g} and remaining coriander to the bowl of onions and toss to coat.

Share your lamb samosas between your plates. Serve the cumin potatoes and pickled onion salad alongside.

Serve your coriander yoghurt in a #dipping bowl{} on the side. Enjoy!